Criteria followed for bird species identificaition based on DNA sequence quality. Categories: 'A' =  > 150 base pairs and > 99% similarity; 'B' = > 150 bp and 90 - 99 % similarity where the next species' similarity is further than 3%; 'C' = samples with > 150 bp or > 90 - 99 % similarity where the next species' similarity is between 2-3% distance; 'E' = > 150 bp and 90 - 99 % similarity where the next species' similarity is smaller than 2% distance but is absent in the geographical area;  'low_bp_similarity': samples with < 150 bp or < 90 - 99 % similarity (not considered for analysis).
